  "prompt": "If you are a chief financial officer of a start up, is that an employee position?",
  "response": "Yes, a Chief Financial Officer (CFO) is typically an employee position within a company, even in a startup. As an executive-level role, the CFO is a key member of the leadership team and is responsible for managing the financial actions of the company. While some startups might initially use a part-time or consulting CFO, most eventually hire a full-time CFO as an employee when they reach a certain stage of growth. In some cases, especially in very early-stage startups, a CFO might also be a co-founder or have an equity stake in addition to being an employee.",
